cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the use of deep learning to automate the management of data center network topologies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on developing a framework for configuring and training deep learning agents. The paper also discusses the use of heuristics, which suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the design and architecture of data center networks, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of deep learning for solving data center problems also suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on data center networks, which could place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
